FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE, BUFFALO - SWAZILAND
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Sat, 25 Oct 1997 10:34:15 +0200
From: Dr. R.D. Paskin <paskin@iafrica.com.na>
Source: Animal Health Surveillance & Development Division, Windhoek

SPECIAL REPORT: FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN SWAZILAND
Please be advised that foot and mouth disease (FMD) has been detected in 2
of a herd of 33 buffalo on Makhaya Game Reserve, Swaziland. The SAT1 virus
was detected
serologically; date of first infection estimated 13 October 1997. The
buffalo run together with other game species and a herd of indigenous Nguni
cattle. Evidence of transmission has so far not been found, but the
reserve is under quarantine and surrounding areas under strict
surveillance. The game reserve is located in the lowlands of southeastern
Swaziland.
[This message has been faxed/e-mailed to countries at risk and a special
SADC Animal Diseases Bulletin was posted to all member states today -RP]
--
Roger Paskin
e-mail: paskin@iafrica.com.na
